Title: My Life as a Dog
Writer: Reidar Jönsson, Lasse Hallström, Brasse Brännström
Actors: Anton Glanzelius, Tomas von Brömssen, Anki Lidén
Plot: In the late '50s, young Ingemar learns a lot about life and himself when he is sent away from his sick mother to live with his aunt and uncle in a town full of eccentrics.
Awards: Nominated for 2 Oscars. 15 wins & 5 nominations total
